68	/// Family-stem base for canonical depots; six-digit auto-increment suffix per
69	/// run. Depots persist post-success for operator inspection; reruns pick the
70	/// next free suffix by walking depot_list output. Per-station tincture is
71	/// composed in at runtime so each station's monikers fact-file-walk against
72	/// a disjoint family stem. Era-bumped past `canest` and `canest2` to
73	/// side-step pending-delete projectId reservations from burned-bridges
74	/// teardown. The `canest2` bump was forced when the prior gmail-identity
75	/// payor's deleted `canest2bhm100000` depot held the global projectId in
